# Walkthrough: Restoring Admin Access

I have implemented a fix for the login issue caused by a synchronization mismatch between Supabase's internal authentication system and your database profiles.

## Steps to Restore Access

### 1. Run the Rescue Script
To fix the account, you need to run the following SQL script in your **Supabase SQL Editor**:

[rescue_admin_access.sql](file:///c:/Users/midhl/Downloads/Our%20Home%20Tuition/rescue_admin_access.sql)

> [!NOTE]
> Make sure you run this in the **SQL Editor** tab of your Supabase dashboard, selecting the `postgres` role if prompted.

### 2. Verify Database State
After running the script, the bottom of the SQL results should show:
- 1 row in `auth.users` with email `ourhometuition.web@gmail.com`
- 1 row in `public.profiles` with email `ourhometuition.web@gmail.com` and role `admin`

### 3. Log In
Open your local application at the preview URL:
[http://localhost:5174/admin/login](http://localhost:5174/admin/login)

![Admin Login Page](C:/Users/midhl/.gemini/antigravity/brain/55b03591-aeea-4f59-8a1f-2aadf3174233/admin_login_page_1773404253953.png)

Use the following credentials:
- **Email**: `ourhometuition.web@gmail.com`
- **Password**: `Ourhometuition@123`

